Rails mass assignment.recommendation:
To avoid this, Rails provides two class methods in your Active Record class to control access to your attributes. The attr_protected method takes a list of attributes that will not be accessible for mass-assignment .A much better way, because it follows the whitelist-principle, is the attr_accessible method. It is the exact opposite of attr_protected, because it takes a list of attributes that will be accessible. All other attributes will be protected. This way you won't forget to protect attributes when adding new ones in the course of development. Here is an example:&lt;code&gt;&lt;pre&gt;
attr_accessible :name
attr_accessible :name, :is_admin, :as =&gt; :admin
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;

